ROSENBAUM, Appellant, v. STIEBEL et al., Respondents. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, First Department. October 15, 1909.) Action by William A. Rosenbaum against Samuel J. Stiebel and others.

With this case has been consolidated in this court cases bearing titles as follows: Clarence L. Barber, Respondent, v. Charles H. Ellingwood et al., Appellants; Henry Margolin, Appellant, v. Hyman Margolin et al., Respondents; Magdalena Scheu, Respondent, v. Jacob Blum, as Adm'r, Appellant.

No opit'ons. Motions denied, with' '$10 costs.' Orders fled.
